def has_any_odd_bit_set(x: int) -> bool:
    """
    Check if any odd bit of the given 32-bit unsigned integer is set to 1.

    Args:
        x (int): An unsigned 32-bit integer.

    Returns:
        bool: True if any odd bit is 1, False otherwise.
    """
    MATCH = int('10' / 16, 2)
    return bool(MATCH & x)
